2.4.1 ‘gnosis-dir’
------------------

The gnosis data directory.  This is where ‘gnosis.db’ is stored.  It is
also the root used for version control when ‘gnosis-vc-auto-push’ is
enabled.  Defaults to ‘{user-emacs-directory}/gnosis/’.

     (setopt gnosis-dir (expand-file-name "gnosis/" user-emacs-directory))


File: gnosis.info,  Node: gnosis-nodes-dir,  Next: gnosis-journal-dir,  Prev: gnosis-dir,  Up: Key Directories

2.4.2 ‘gnosis-nodes-dir’
------------------------

The directory containing your note files.  All ‘.org’ and ‘.org.gpg’
files in this directory are indexed by gnosis.  Defaults to ‘~/Notes/’.

     (setopt gnosis-nodes-dir "~/Notes/")


File: gnosis.info,  Node: gnosis-journal-dir,  Prev: gnosis-nodes-dir,  Up: Key Directories

2.4.3 ‘gnosis-journal-dir’
--------------------------

The directory for journal entry files.  Defaults to a ‘journal/’
subdirectory inside ‘gnosis-nodes-dir’.  Journal files are indexed
separately from regular nodes but use the same underlying mechanism.

     (setopt gnosis-journal-dir (expand-file-name "journal/" gnosis-nodes-dir))


