3 Nodes
*******

Nodes are gnosis's note-taking system.  A node is an org-mode heading
(or an entire org file) that has been assigned an org ID.  Gnosis
indexes all nodes in its database, enabling fast search, tag-based
browsing, backlink navigation, and linking from themata.

   The node system is deliberately minimal.  Files live on disk as plain
org-mode files, readable and editable without gnosis.  The database is a
derived index that can be rebuilt at any time from the files themselves.

